Xinhua Stock Indices Drop 
Both Xinhua A and B Stock indices, indicators of operation for China's
securities market, fell today.
The A stock index closed at 25.98, 1.22 points lower than the figure
for the last trading day, and the B stock index dropped by 0.69 points
to close at 37.50.
The Xinhua stock index is the country's first national unitary stock
exponent, which is jointly designed and issued by the Economic
Information Department of Xinhua News Agency and Beijing University.
